The paper deals with a wireless network model and proposes achievable strategies and outer bounds for a general Interference Channel with Generalized Feedback (IFC-GF) with two source-destination pairs. The paper focuses on exploiting the feedback to gain knowledge about the message sent by other users and then using it to relay or hide messages. This involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication (cs.COM).
